1. Write a new REST API test
Step 1 — Open (or create) a .feature file under:


application-tests/src/test/resources/features/
Step 2 — Write the scenario in plain English:


@mosaic @smoke
Feature: Mosaic Config API

  Background:
    Given the "mosaic" API is available

  Scenario: Register API key returns HTTP 200
    When I send a "POST" request to "/api/Config/apiKey?apiKey=MosaicService_apikey"
    Then the response HTTP status should be 200
    And the response root should match these values:
      | isSuccessStatusCode | true |
      | reasonPhrase        | OK   |
      | statusCode          | 200  |
Step 3 — Add the service URL to the environment file:


application-tests/src/test/resources/environments/qa.json

"apiServices": {
  "mosaic": {
    "baseUrl": "http://mosaiclnqa01:5000",
    "timeoutMs": 30000
  }
}
Step 4 — Run it:


mvn test -pl application-tests -Dcucumber.filter.tags="@mosaic" -Denv=qa
2. Run tests by profile

# Smoke only — fast, critical path, every commit
mvn test -pl application-tests -Dcucumber.filter.tags="@smoke" -Denv=qa

# Full regression — nightly
mvn test -pl application-tests -Dcucumber.filter.tags="@regression" -Denv=qa

# Specific API only
mvn test -pl application-tests -Dcucumber.filter.tags="@mosaic" -Denv=qa
mvn test -pl application-tests -Dcucumber.filter.tags="@stp" -Denv=qa
mvn test -pl application-tests -Dcucumber.filter.tags="@finance" -Denv=qa

# All API tests together
mvn test -pl application-tests -Dcucumber.filter.tags="@mosaic or @stp or @finance" -Denv=qa

# Everything except work-in-progress and intentionally broken demos
mvn test -pl application-tests \
  -Dcucumber.filter.tags="not @wip and not @ignore and not @failing" \
  -Denv=qa
