4. Auto-generate tests from a Swagger / OpenAPI spec

# From a remote Swagger URL
./generate-bdd.sh --url http://mosaiclnqa01:5000/swagger.json

# From a local spec file (YAML or JSON)
./generate-bdd.sh --file ./specs/my-api.yaml

# Custom output file name
./generate-bdd.sh --url http://mosaiclnqa01:5000/swagger.json \
  --output mosaic-api.feature

# Custom output directory
./generate-bdd.sh --url http://mosaiclnqa01:5000/swagger.json \
  --output-dir application-tests/src/test/resources/features/triforce

# Add extra tags to every generated scenario
./generate-bdd.sh --url http://mosaiclnqa01:5000/swagger.json \
  --tags @mosaic,@sprint42

# Overwrite an existing file
./generate-bdd.sh --url http://mosaiclnqa01:5000/swagger.json --overwrite
Generated scenarios are tagged @wip @ignore by default — review them, remove @ignore from the ones you want to run, then:


mvn test -pl application-tests \
  -Dcucumber.filter.tags="@autogenerated and not @ignore" -Denv=qa
